  "body": "### Component\n\nFoundryup\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (e881b75 2022-03-25T00:07:41.456668+00:00)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nfoundryup -b master\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (amd)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nSteps to reproduce:\r\n1. Use `foundryup` to switch to a branch, such as `foundryup -b revm` (when testing https://github.com/gakonst/foundry/pull/918)\r\n2. That branch later gets deleted\r\n3. Run `foundryup -b master` which fails with:\r\n\r\n```\r\nYour configuration specifies to merge with the ref 'refs/heads/revm'\r\nfrom the remote, but no such ref was fetched.\r\n```\r\n\r\nI fixed this by `cd`'ing into `~/.foundry/gakonst/foundry` and manually switch to the latest master, then run `foundryup -b revm`, so presumably a similar approach can be implemented in the foundryup script",
