    "body": "Strange, I cannot reproduce this.\r\n\r\n1. I created a branch `onbjerg/test` with some changes\r\n2. Ran `foundryup -b onbjerg/test`\r\n3. Deleted the branch\r\n4. Ran `foundryup -b master`\r\n5. No error\r\n\r\nDo you have some global git config set that changes this behavior, and if so, do you think doing\r\n\r\n```\r\ngit switch $BRANCH\r\ngit fetch\r\ngit reset --hard origin/$BRANCH\r\n```\r\n\r\nWould work? Currently we do\r\n\r\n```\r\ngit fetch\r\ngit reset --hard origin/$BRANCH\r\n```",
