    "body": "> Strange, I cannot reproduce this.\r\n\r\nHuh interesting, I should be able to give this another try later—it's possible I had something funky going on and perhaps https://github.com/gakonst/foundry/pull/1047 helped\r\n\r\n> Do you have some global git config set that changes this behavior, and if so, do you think doing\r\n\r\nLooking now, the only thing that may be related here is that I have `defaultBranch = main` under `[init]`, but from a quick look at the foundryup script I don't think that should be related\r\n\r\nI do think running `git switch $BRANCH` first would help since that resolved it in my case, and from googling the git error that seems to be a commonly suggested solution on stackoverflow.\r\n\r\nAs a side note (perhaps I should create a separate issue): Not sure if you use the GitHub CLI, but using `gh pr checkout <prNumber>` is super great. It works seamlessly even when the branch on that PR is from a fork. I'd love a similar feature for foundryup so you can do `foundryup -pr 1048`. Seems I can't get foundryup to checkout that branch:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ foundryup --repo mattse/dapptools-rs -b matt/flush-cache\r\nCloning into 'dapptools-rs'...\r\nremote: Repository not found.\r\nfatal: repository 'https://github.com/mattse/dapptools-rs/' not found\r\n```",
